ref: https://help.dreamhost.com/hc/en-us/articles/215489338-Installing-and-using-Python-s-virtualenv

Install 'pip' and other necessary ones
  $ sudo apt-get install python-pip python-dev build-essential
  $ sudo pip install --upgrade pip 
  $ sudo pip install --upgrade virtualenv 

It is possible to create virtual env for a local user python and a system installed python

Make a dir for the environment (where all the files needed will be copied)
  $ mkdir pythn_virtenv
 
Goto the dir
  $ cd python_virtenv

Create the virtual env (if you use python then the system installed(if the python path is not changed in bash profile file))
  $ virtualenv -p python <proj_name>
    
Activate env
  $ source <proj_name>/bin/activate
  // Now a shell will be there with the name of the project

To deactivate 
  $ deactivate
  
To remove
  $ rm -rf <pathToFolder>/<proj_name>/



  
